data.enText: the chance of sth happening; how likely sth is to happen

data.chText: 几乎没有发生那种事情的可能。
data.enText: There is very little likelihood of that happening.

data.chText: 这次会议十有八九要被取消。
data.enText: In all likelihood (= very probably) the meeting will be cancelled.

data.chText: 很有可能失业人数会继续下降。
data.enText: The likelihood is that (= it is likely that) unemployment figures will continue to fall.

simple_means.memory_skill: likely 可能的 + hood 性质 → 可能性

tr: the probability of a specified outcome

value.def: The likelihood of something happening is how likely it is to happen.

example.ex: The likelihood of infection is minimal...
There didn't seem much likelihood of it happening...
example.tran: 这种事情发生的可能性不大。

example.ex: There is every likelihood that sanctions will work.
example.tran: 制裁完全可能发挥作用。

value.def: If something is a likelihood, it is likely to happen.

example.ex: But the likelihood is that people would be willing to pay if they were certain that their money was going to a good cause...
example.tran: 但如果人们确切知道自己的钱会用于做善事，他们就可能更愿意掏腰包。

example.ex: That, as we all know, is not only a possibility but a likelihood.
example.tran: 众所周知，那不仅可能发生，而且是很可能发生。

value.def: If you say that something will happen in all likelihood, you mean that it will probably happen.

example.ex: In all likelihood, the committee will have to interview every woman who's worked with Thomas.
example.tran: 十有八九，委员会将不得不与每一位曾和托马斯共过事的女性面谈。
